issue.body:
The constructor code is as follows:

``` C++
  StunAttrAddr(const StunAttrIterator &iter) : StunAttr(iter) {

    if (iter.eof())
      throw EndOfStunMsgException();
    size_t sz = 0;
    const uint8_t *buf = iter.getRawBuffer(sz);
    if (stun_attr_get_addr_str(buf, sz, getSar(iter), &_addr, NULL) < 0) {
      throw WrongStunAttrFormatException();
    }
  }
```

The `buf` in the code is actually the value of the Attribute. However, the `buf` that `stun_attr_get_addr_str` needs is a full STUN Message and needs to get the `stun_tid` from that `buf`.

